  "text": "The 'upstream connection pool overflow' error in Envoy occurs when resource limits are exceeded and connection pooling cannot accommodate new requests. The condition is defined and handled across multiple layers:\n\n**Definition Layer:**\nThe overflow state is defined as `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` enum value in `envoy/common/conn_pool.h` (line 98), indicating that a resource overflowed and policy prevented a new connection from being created.\n\n**Emission Points (Where overflow is triggered):**\n\n1. **Stream-level overflow** in `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc`:\n   - `ConnPoolImplBase::attachStreamToClient()` (lines 175-180): Triggered when the max streams limit is exceeded, checked via `resourceManager().requests().canCreate()`. Logs \"max streams overflow\" and increments `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` statistic.\n   - `ConnPoolImplBase::newStreamImpl()` (lines 282-287): Triggered when max pending streams overflow is detected via `resourceManager().pendingRequests().canCreate()`. Logs \"max pending streams overflow\".\n\n2. **Connection pool-level overflow** in `source/common/upstream/conn_pool_map_impl.h`:\n   - `ConnPoolMap<KEY_TYPE, POOL_TYPE>::getPool()` (lines 33-40): When attempting to create a new connection pool entry but the pool limit is reached and no idle pool can be freed, increments the `upstream_cx_pool_overflow_` counter (defined in `envoy/upstream/upstream.h`).\n\n**Handling/Propagation Chain:**\n\nWhen overflow is detected:\n1. The base connection pool calls `onPoolFailure()` with `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`\n2. This propagates through HTTP protocol implementations via the connection pool callbacks\n3. `MultiplexedActiveClientBase::onStreamReset()` in `source/common/http/conn_pool_base.cc` (line 178) receives the overflow reset reason\n4. The router filter in `source/common/router/router.cc` handles the overflow:\n   - `Filter::resetReasonToResponseFlag()` (line 1466) maps `StreamResetReason::Overflow` to `StreamInfo::CoreResponseFlag::UpstreamOverflow`\n   - Sets the response flag indicating upstream overflow occurred (line 554)\n\nThe complete flow shows overflow as a resource management mechanism that prevents cascade failures during traffic spikes by rejecting new requests when connection pools reach configured limits."
}

